The Americans believe that this time their raw power can impose regime change on an enemy without creating a disaster.

02:39.000 --> 02:51.000
The removal of Iraq's Saddam Hussein in 2003 led to a catastrophe, long years of war that incubated jihadist extremist movements that still exist.

02:52.000 --> 03:04.000
The Americans released video of their targets with Israel they believe the economic and political weakness of the Islamic regime in Iran gives them an opportunity to strike that they have to take.

03:04.000 --> 03:16.000
Israel and the US went back to war with Iran just after breakfast time in Tehran hitting the capital and sites across the country.

03:17.000 --> 03:24.000
It's hard to get information about what's happening there. Video of an attack on a school in southern Iran is circulating.

03:24.000 --> 03:34.000
Iranian State TV was reporting 85 killed.This is a dangerous moment with unpredictable consequences in the world's most turbulent region.

03:35.000 --> 03:43.000
Israel said the whole operation is a preemptive attack without producing evidence of an imminent threat.

03:43.000 --> 03:54.000
Siren sounded immediately in Israel.War is political and this is a war of choice aimed at changing the regime in Iran.

03:58.000 --> 04:08.000
Iran tried to deliver on its thread of a devastating response aimed at the extensive network of US bases in the Gulf.This was Qatar as well as Israel.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
Go go go.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Get in get inside.

04:12.000 --> 04:19.000
In Dubai tourists looking for winter sun had a nasty reminder of the region's realities.

04:20.000 --> 04:31.000
Close by in Bahrain this appears to be a strike aimed at the big US naval base.Iran says it will use more powerful missiles than the ones it fired in last summer's war.

04:32.000 --> 04:41.000
An interceptor rocket went up.Iran will hope that as the days passed the US and Israel will start running out of defensive missiles.

04:44.000 --> 04:51.000
In Tehran regime supporters rallied around the flag.It would take more than killing the supreme leader to destroy the regime.

04:51.000 --> 04:59.000
It has a complex political system underpinned by ideology corruption and the ruthless use of force against the sent.

05:02.000 --> 05:10.000
In January big protests against the regime and the economic crisis were crushed with live bullets that killed thousands of people.

05:10.000 --> 05:20.000
Donald Trump promised to protect them and seems to believe that the regime will fall if they try again after America and Israel's onslaught.

05:21.000 --> 05:33.000
At dusk the Fairmont Hotel on Dubai's Palm was hit.It isn't clear if it was targeted or if this was caused by missile debris from an interception the fire took hold.

05:36.000 --> 05:49.000
And this was Bahrain.More devastation.Iran has a big arsenal of accurate short range missiles.Iran's leaders will now be calculating how to write out the war,how to survive and how to manage.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
It's consequences.

05:57.000 --> 06:09.000
Well tonight the United Nations Security Council is holding an emergency meeting to discuss today's extraordinary events and these are live pictures from the session in New York.

06:09.000 --> 06:18.000
The Secretary General Antonio Guterres warned that today's military action risks triggering uncontrollable consequences for the Middle East.

06:20.000 --> 06:33.000
Well this evening Donald Trump said he believes a large number of Iran's leaders have also been killed.The president said the operation has been a success.Let's go live to Sarah Smith who's at the White House Forest tonight.

