Just hours earlier he was campaigning in Texas in a hamburger joint giving no hint of the planned assault.

08:19.000 --> 08:24.000
I'm going to get some stuff for Air Force One and I'm going to get the hell out of here all right.

08:29.000 --> 08:35.000
Not much later he was describing how he plans to stop Iran developing a nuclear weapon.

08:35.000 --> 08:40.000
We're going to destroy their missiles and raise their missile industry to the ground.

08:40.000 --> 08:45.000
It will be totally again obliterated.

08:45.000 --> 08:50.000
Last year President Trump addressed thousands of American troops stationed in the Middle East

08:50.000 --> 08:53.000
telling them his priorities to end conflicts not start them.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.000
Now he's warning of casualties and fatalities.

08:56.000 --> 09:04.000
The lives of courageous American heroes may be lost and we may have casualties that often happens in war.

09:04.000 --> 09:11.000
But we're doing this not for now we're doing this for the future and it is a noble mission.

09:11.000 --> 09:17.000
When the US launched B-2 bombers to attack Iran last year the action was limited to nuclear sites.

09:17.000 --> 09:22.000
Now he says the Iranian people have the chance to overthrow the ruling regime.

09:22.000 --> 09:31.000
Now is the time to seize control of your destiny and to unleash the prosperous and glorious future that is close within your reach.

09:31.000 --> 09:35.000
This is the moment for action do not let it pass.

09:36.000 --> 09:42.000
Donald Trump has railed against previous American attempts at regime change in Iraq and Afghanistan.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
He is not planning to invade Iran.

09:44.000 --> 09:49.000
He hopes he can overthrow its leadership without putting American boots on the ground.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
Sara Smith BBC News Washington

09:51.000 --> 10:03.000
Well in the Iranian capital Tehran there's been loud cheers to celebrate the reported death of the country's supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei

10:03.000 --> 10:07.000
has been the figurehead of the Islamic Republic for more than three decades.

10:07.000 --> 10:12.000
Seven missiles hit the presidential palace and there have been strikes around his compound.

10:12.000 --> 10:19.000
Bharana Basi from the BBC's Persian Service reports now in a warning it contains distressing images.

10:21.000 --> 10:25.000
Cheers ringing out from residential buildings in Tehran.

10:25.000 --> 10:31.000
After Israeli media reported the death of Iran's supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei.

10:31.000 --> 10:36.000
Claims Tehran has dismissed as psychological warfare.

10:36.000 --> 10:44.000
News that if confirmed would be welcomed by many Iranians who suffered under his rule for nearly four decades.

10:44.000 --> 10:47.000
This is how the day began.

10:47.000 --> 10:57.000
Panic on the streets of Tehran around 9.40am a working day in Iran when loud explosions were heard across the country.

10:57.000 --> 11:01.000
War has started near our office down in Palestine street.

11:01.000 --> 11:03.000
All the buildings were shaking.

11:03.000 --> 11:06.000
The streets are full of terrified people.

11:06.000 --> 11:15.000
At the same time a sense of relief for some and at this school teenagers celebrate.

11:15.000 --> 11:28.000
In early January shocking pictures were shared with the world of thousands of people killed when government forces opened fire on protesters calling for regime change.

11:28.000 --> 11:34.000
The brutality left many believing only military intervention could topple the regime.

11:34.000 --> 11:40.000
But public sentiment could shift sharply if civilians are killed in the attacks.

11:40.000 --> 11:48.000
Many Iranians reacted with anger after state media reported that an Israeli strike on a girl's school killed dozens.

11:48.000 --> 11:53.000
